> The Stdcpp target

The stdcpp (standard c++) target allows you to write command line utilities in Monkey.

>> You will need

* (Windows) [The MinGW compiler collection](http://tdm-gcc.tdragon.net/download).

* (MacOS) [XCode 3.2.5 or later](http://developer.apple.com/devcenter/mac/index.action).

>> Notes

On Windows, you will need to set the `MINGW` var in your [[Trans]] config file. This should point to the actual MinGW directory, not the 'bin' sub-directory.
